(47, 'Susana Domingos', 'susana.domingos@ipt.pt', '091A-A703-3B66', 'Susana Caetano Domingos, PhD in Education from the University of Lisbon. Her initial training is the Degree in English and German Teaching from the University of Minho. Post-Graduated in Supervision and Pedagogical Guidance and certified as a professor trainer by the Scientific Pedagogical Council for Continuing Education (CCPFC/RFO – 36874/16), in areas B02 (Evaluation); B09 (Organization of the education system); C05 (Specific didactics). International Certified Professional Coach (Coach S905-2019 PT) by the Institute of Behavioral and Management Sciences, she anchors her knowledge in the area of emotional intelligence, positive psychology and neuro-linguistic programming (NLP), knowledge consolidated in several nationally and internationally recognized trainings. At the moment she\'s attending the Master in Psychology at the University of Wolverhampton. She has been dedicated, in addition to the specific area of education and teaching/learning in higher education, to the study of various themes related to personal and professional development, such as the multiple intelligence theories, emotional intelligence, critical incidents, reflection and change, producing national and international communications and publications. ', 'Susana Caetano Domingos, PhD in Education from the University of Lisbon. Her initial training is the Degree in English and German Teaching from the University of Minho. Post-Graduated in Supervision and Pedagogical Guidance and certified as a professor trainer by the Scientific Pedagogical Council for Continuing Education (CCPFC/RFO – 36874/16), in areas B02 (Evaluation); B09 (Organization of the education system); C05 (Specific didactics). International Certified Professional Coach (Coach S905-2019 PT) by the Institute of Behavioral and Management Sciences, she anchors her knowledge in the area of emotional intelligence, positive psychology and neuro-linguistic programming (NLP), knowledge consolidated in several nationally and internationally recognized trainings. At the moment she\'s attending the Master in Psychology at the University of Wolverhampton. She has been dedicated, in addition to the specific area of education and teaching/learning in higher education, to the study of various themes related to personal and professional development, such as the multiple intelligence theories, emotional intelligence, critical incidents, reflection and change, producing national and international communications and publications. ', 'Integrado', '65aef3d039de7_mw-1920.webp', '.', '.', '0000-0002-6351-5728', '', '', '', '$2y$10$e0A0qn10Stw6C1uIjol9QOUqgle9Nw7r6/WUZtRdvpiZ6eaJLYJfC', NULL),
(48, 'Anícia Rebelo Trindade', 'anicia.r.trindade@gmail.com', '7115-2BBE-DE87', 'Investigadora Integrada no Centro para a Tecnologia, Restauro e Valorização das Artes (TECHN&ART). Ocupa um cargo  de Técnica Superior na Agência para a Modernização Administrativa, no departamento responsável pela prestação de serviços digitais nos Espaços Cidadão. É licenciada em Ciências da Educação, Mestre  em Tecnologias Educativas,  pós-graduada em Empreendedorismo e Gestão da Inovação e  Doutorada em Educação Multimédia, com especialização em Competência Digital.\r\n\r\n Colaborou como Designer Instrucional em diferentes projetos educativos para o ensino a distância (EaD). Participou igualmente em vários projetos relacionados com turismo sustentável, gestão e inovação digital em diferentes contextos. No que diz respeito à avaliação e certificação de competências digitais, desde 2009, trabalhou como especialista no reconhecimento e validação de competências, estando profundamente envolvida em projetos relacionados com a utilização do Quadro Europeru de Competência Digital:  DigComp 2.2. É também membro de algumas organizações internacionais e nacionais na área da competência digital (Europeana, ALL Digital), aconselhando e revendo qualificações padrão e garantia da qualidade. \r\n\r\nComo Gestora de Projetos de Inovação, trabalhou em estreita colaboração com diferentes organizações e países da Europa, sendo convidada a participar e colaborar em várias consultas e análises de projetos. Esta experiência permitiu-lhe desenvolver excelentes competências de comunicação verbal e escrita. Coordenou e geriu projetos e cursos de formação nas seguintes áreas: Turismo Arqueológico, Turismo Sustentável, Competência Digital, Gestão de projetos, empreendedorismo, inteligência emocional e serviços eletrónicos. \r\n\r\nAtualmente, está a trabalhar numa Pós-Graduação Pós-Doutoral relacionada com a inovação e gestão de projetos de turismo sustentável na Universidade de Coimbra e no Centro para a Tecnologia, Restauro e Valorização das Artes (Techn&Art) - Instituto Politécnico de Tomar. É uma profissional muito dedicada e criativa, com um elevado sentido de responsabilidade e liderança.', 'Integrated Researcher at the Centre for Technology, Restoration, and Art Enhancement (TECHN&ART). She holds a position as a Senior Technician at the Agency for Administrative Modernization,  at the department of digital services at Citizen Spots. She has a degree in Educational Sciences, a Master’s in Educational Technologies, a postgraduate degree in Entrepreneurship and Innovation Management, and a Ph.D. in Multimedia Education, specializing in Digital Competence. She has worked as an Instructional Designer on different distance learning projects and has been involved in projects related to sustainable tourism, management, and digital innovation.\r\n\r\nSince 2009, she has specialized in the assessment and certification of digital competencies, playing a significant role in projects utilizing the European Digital Competence Framework: DigComp 2.2. She is an active member of several international and national organizations focused on digital competence, where she provides expert advice and reviews standard qualifications and quality assurance.\r\n\r\nAs an Innovation Project Manager, she has collaborated with numerous organizations and countries across Europe, participating in various project consultations and analyses. This extensive experience has honed her excellent verbal and written communication skills. She has coordinated and managed projects and training courses in areas such as Archaeological Tourism, Sustainable Tourism, Digital Competence, Project Management, Entrepreneurship, Emotional Intelligence, and Electronic Services.\r\n\r\nCurrently, she is pursuing a Post-Doctoral Graduation focused on innovation and sustainable tourism project management at Coimbra University and the Centre for Technology, Restoration, and Art Enhancement (Techn&Art) at the Polytechnic Institute of Tomar. She is known for her dedication, creativity, strong sense of responsibility, and leadership abilities.', 'Integrado', '6659f8e9323a3_1632710285395.jpg', 'Design Instrucional, Formação e Educação a Distância, Turismo Sustentável, Competência Digital, Inovação Digital, Competências Digitais, IoT, Inteligência Artificial, Frameworks Sustentáveis, Gestão de Projetos.', 'Instructional Design, Training and Distance Education, Sustainable Tourism, Digital Competence, Digital Innovation, Digital Skills, IoT, Artificial Intelligence, Sustainable Frameworks, Project Management.', '0000-0001-8180-3929', '', '', '', '$2y$10$FFkIu5.2WfkRVDKoNqoTouo0qzCsZDxiTYzIhMFUXeV95YnkcQDiC', NULL);
