(49, 'Silviu Miloiu', 'silviu.miloiu@valahia.ro', '9A18-0737-97D2', 'Professor Silviu Miloiu (silviumiloiu.hypotheses.org) é diretor do Centro de Investigação “Grigore Gafencu” para Relações Internacionais e Estudos de Património da Universidade Valahia de Târgoviște. É também Presidente da Associação Romena de Estudos Bálticos e Nórdicos e editor-chefe do Jornal Romeno de Estudos Bálticos e Nórdicos. Além disso, lidera a Equipa de Projetos da Universidade Valahia dentro da Universidade Europeia KreativEU, que ele iniciou.\r\n\r\nDesde 2010, o Professor Miloiu organiza uma conferência anual sobre Estudos Bálticos e Nórdicos na Romênia, que se estabeleceu como o maior evento desse tipo no Sudeste da Europa. Ele recebeu diversas medalhas e prêmios do Reino Unido, Finlândia, Letônia e Lituânia em reconhecimento às suas contribuições significativas aos estudos bálticos e nórdicos, bem como aos estudos britânicos.\r\n\r\nComo supervisor de doutorado em história, o Professor Miloiu presidiu 17 dissertações de doutorado defendidas com sucesso e atualmente supervisiona cinco candidatos a Ph.D. Várias dessas dissertações foram co-defendidas ou estão em andamento em colaboração com instituições de prestígio, incluindo a Université Sorbonne Nouvelle – Paris 3 e a Universidade de Stuttgart.', 'Professor Silviu Miloiu (silviumiloiu.hypotheses.org) serves as the director of the “Grigore Gafencu” Research Center for International Relations and Heritage Studies at Valahia University of Târgoviște. He is also the president of the Romanian Association of Baltic and Nordic Studies and the editor-in-chief of the Romanian Journal for Baltic and Nordic Studies. In addition, he leads the Valahia University Project Team within the KreativEU European University project, which he initiated.\r\nSince 2010, he has organized an annual conference on Baltic and Nordic Studies in Romania, which has become the largest event of its kind in Southeastern Europe. Professor Silviu Miloiu has received various medals and awards from the UK, Finland, Latvia, and Lithuania in recognition of his contributions to Baltic and Nordic studies, as well as British studies. \r\nAs a Ph.D. supervisor in history, Professor Silviu Miloiu has chaired 17 successfully defended doctoral dissertations and currently supervises five Ph.D. candidates. Some of these dissertations have been co-defended or are in progress in collaboration with prestigious institutions such as Université Sorbonne Nouvelle – Paris 3 and the University of Stuttgart.', 'Colaborador', '66faf394cb8d9_Silviu.jpg', 'A pesquisa do Professor Silviu Miloiu especializa-se em história da política externa romena nos séculos XX e XXI, bem como na história báltica e nórdica, nas relações da Roménia com os países bálticos e nórdicos, na história das minorias na Europa Central e Oriental, e no património cultural. Liderou inúmeros projetos de pesquisa nacionais e internacionais nesses domínios e é autor de várias monografias, capítulos e artigos, além de volumes de documentos publicados na Roménia, nos países bálticos e nórdicos, e em outros lugares da Europa e dos Estados Unidos.\r\n\r\nSeu trabalho académico inclui mais de 30 livros — seja como autor, editor ou coautor — e mais de 100 artigos e capítulos científicos publicados nacional e internacionalmente. Dirigiu vários projetos de investigação e foi o organizador principal de mais de 20 conferências internacionais.', 'Professor Silviu Miloiu\'s research specializes in the history of Romanian foreign policy in the 20th and 21st centuries, as well as Baltic and Nordic history, Romania\'s relations with the Baltic and Nordic countries, the history of minorities in East Central Europe, and cultural heritage. He has led numerous national and international research projects within these domains and has authored several monographs, chapters, and articles, as well as volumes of documents published in Romania, the Baltic and Nordic countries, and elsewhere in Europe and the United States.\r\nHis scholarly work includes over 30 books—either authored, edited, or co-authored—and more than 100 scientific articles and chapters published nationally and internationally. He has directed several research projects and has been the primary organizer of over 20 international conferences.', ' https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0472-4212', 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=QT-AWFAAAAAJ&hl=en', 'https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Silviu-Marian-Miloiu-2', '44661445300', '$2y$10$mnZHyGLcbizzNr3D00R6RuCCQU3uqqyx137dG5560P4X3bZgRJm9m', NULL),
(50, 'António Pereira Pais', 'antoniopais@ipcb.pt', '0E11-6B37-C5B9', 'António Pereira Pais (antoniopais@ipcb.pt) é doutor em Ciências da Educação pelo Departamento de Didática da Faculdade de Educação da Universidade Complutense de Madrid, desde 2001.\r\n\r\nÉ Professor Adjunto na Escola Superior de Educação do Instituto Politécnico de Castelo de Castelo Branco desde 2007, lecionando nos cursos Licenciatura em Português – protocolo Universidade Politécnica de Macau (UPM) / IPCB; Licenciatura em Educação Básica IPCB/ESE; Mestrado em Educação Pré-Escolar e Ensino do 1.º CEB - IPCB/ESE; Licenciatura em Secretariado - IPCB/ESE, sendo responsável científico das unidades curriculares no âmbito da Didática Língua e coordenador da Prática de Ensino Supervisionada no Ensino Básico (1.º CEB).\r\n\r\nÉ membro integrado do Centro de Investigação em Património, Educação e Cultura (CIPEC), desenvolvendo investigação no âmbito da Didática Integrada e da Didática da Língua, participando como investigador especialista e consultor científico em projetos de investigação nacionais e internacionais.\r\n', 'António Pereira Pais (antoniopais@ipcb.pt) has a PhD in Educational Sciences from the Department of Didactics of the Faculty of Education of the Complutense University of Madrid, since 2001.\r\n\r\nHe has been an Adjunct Professor at the Higher School of Education of the Polytechnic Institute of Castelo de Castelo Branco since 2007, teaching courses in Portuguese – Macau Polytechnic University (UPM) / IPCB protocol; Degree in Basic Education IPCB/ESE; Master\'s Degree in Pre-School Education and Teaching from the 1st CEB - IPCB/ESE; Degree in Secretariat - IPCB/ESE, being scientific responsible for the curricular units within the scope of Language Didactics and coordinator of Supervised Teaching Practice in Basic Education (1st CEB).\r\n\r\nHe is an integrated member of the Center for Research in Heritage, Education and Culture (CIPEC), developing research within the scope of Integrated Didactics and Language Didactics, participating as a specialist researcher and scientific consultant in national and international research projects.', 'Integrado', '66faa46265d01_1696797266086.jpg', 'Das principais áreas em que trabalha destacam-se:\r\nFormação de Professores\r\nDidática da Língua\r\nEnsino do Vocabulário\r\nLexicultura\r\nPatrimónio e Educação para a preservação.', 'The main areas in which he works include:\r\nTeacher Training\r\nLanguage Didactics\r\nVocabulary Teaching\r\nLexiculture\r\nHeritage and Education for Preservation.', 'https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9240-0682', 'https://scholar.google.com.br/citations?user=d5AZebgAAAAJ&hl=pt-PT', '', '', '$2y$10$.kCGKRpwci2VXYjdqpn8S.u8aVYRdpCrIZEh7.rZRFy/zc0hzUqGm', NULL),
(51, 'Sergiu Musteata', 'sergiu_musteata@yahoo.com', '8E18-4B6D-1B4E ', 'Sergiu MUSTEATA is an archaeologist/historian from the Republic of Moldova, and a professor at the University „Valahia” Târgovi¿te, Romania. He holds his Ph.D. in the History Faculty of „Al.I. Cuza” University, Ia¿i, Romania (1999) and habilitation thesis at the „Ion Creanga” Pedagogical State University of Chisinau (2021). He is a former research fellow of various scholarships in the USA, Hungary, Sweden, and Poland, including DAAD and Humboldt Foundation at Bonn, Freiburg, and Braunschweig universities, Fulbright Scholar at the University of Maryland, University of California Berkeley, and Stanford University. He is the author of 8 monographs, more than 300 scientific publications, editor of over 30 books, and editor of two scientific journals. His major academic interests are Medieval History and Archaeology of Eastern Europe; Cultural Heritage Preservation and History textbook analysis. ', ' ', 'Colaborador', '65aefea8d6492_musteata-2016.jpg', 'Sergiu MUSTEATA is an archaeologist/historian from the Republic of Moldova, and a professor at the University „Valahia” Târgovi¿te, Romania. He holds his Ph.D. in the History Faculty of „Al.I. Cuza” University, Ia¿i, Romania (1999) and habilitation thesis at the „Ion Creanga” Pedagogical State University of Chisinau (2021). He is a former research fellow of various scholarships in the USA, Hungary, Sweden, and Poland, including DAAD and Humboldt Foundation at Bonn, Freiburg, and Braunschweig universities, Fulbright Scholar at the University of Maryland, University of California Berkeley, and Stanford University. He is the author of 8 monographs, more than 300 scientific publications, editor of over 30 books, and editor of two scientific journals. His major academic interests are Medieval History and Archaeology of Eastern Europe; Cultural Heritage Preservation and History textbook analysis. ', ' ', 'N', '', '', '', '$2y$10$m0FOcRUsbfGNxReKiJ2iLOOoxJnyACnw5yR/zFf9282AjpA4.hyMu', NULL),
(52, 'António Manso', 'manso@ipt.pt', 'AE17-1477-51C0', 'António Manuel Rodrigues Manso concluiu o doutoramento em Informática pela Universidade de Lisboa em 2020 e o mestrado em Inteligência Artificial pela Universidade Nova de Lisboa em 2002. É Professor Adjunto no Instituto Politécnico de Tomar e actua na área de Engenharia e Tecnologia com ênfase em sistemas inteligentes. ', 'António Manuel Rodrigues Manso completed his PhD in Computer Science at the University of Lisbon in 2020 and his master\'s degree in Artificial Intelligence at the New University of Lisbon in 2002. He is an Adjunct Professor at the Polytechnic Institute of Tomar and works in the field of Engineering and Technology with an emphasis on intelligent systems.\r\n', 'Integrado', '65aeb039a7663_WhatsApp Image 2024-01-22 at 18.03.00.jpeg', '.', '.', '0000-0003-2504-0642', 'CzMN4DIAAAAJ&hl', 'Antonio-Manso', '', '$2y$10$z3PcSb.O4YPcVTR1y.7b1uOsAzk9NXQjf3PVsXUwNUafNFNoHPbA6', NULL),
(53, 'Sajid Anwar', 'sajid.anwar@imsciences.edu.pk', '891C-00A4-ABBB', 'Sajid Anwar received the B.Sc. and M.Sc. degrees in computer science from the University of Peshawar in 1997 and 1999, respectively, and the M.S. degree in computer science and the Ph.D. degree in software architecture from the University of NUCES-FAST, Pakistan, in 2007 and 2011, respectively. He is currently an Assistant Professor of Computing Science, and a Coordinator of the B.S.-Software Engineering with the Institute of Management Sciences, Peshawar, Pakistan. His research interests are concerned with software architecture, software requirement engineering, searched-based software engineering, and mining software repository.', ' ', 'Colaborador', '65b3e50e2d883_1685340430991.jpg', 'Sajid Anwar received the B.Sc. and M.Sc. degrees in computer science from the University of Peshawar in 1997 and 1999, respectively, and the M.S. degree in computer science and the Ph.D. degree in software architecture from the University of NUCES-FAST, Pakistan, in 2007 and 2011, respectively. He is currently an Assistant Professor of Computing Science, and a Coordinator of the B.S.-Software Engineering with the Institute of Management Sciences, Peshawar, Pakistan. His research interests are concerned with software architecture, software requirement engineering, searched-based software engineering, and mining software repository.', ' ', '0000-0003-3393-1656', '', '', '', '$2y$10$1Y0zbFIVY.FFGVlW8s6WAO.HztBSFFd/aM21dABlKoHiOzXAtRvhC', NULL),
(54, 'Bilge Aksay', 'baksay@atu.edu.tr', 'A612-63BC-ABFF', 'Assoc Prof Bilge Aksay works in Adana Alparslan Türkeş Science and Technology University, Management Information Systems Department. She studies entrepreneurship, research methods and organizational behavior. She is giving lectures on both bachelor degree and master degree programmes.', 'Assoc Prof Bilge Aksay works in Adana Alparslan Türkeş Science and Technology University, Management Information Systems Department. She studies entrepreneurship, research methods and organizational behavior. She is giving lectures on both bachelor degree and master degree programmes.', 'Colaborador', '65b3e420cd8c6_picture.jpeg', '.', '.', '0000-0002-0563-7778', 'https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=9pZX2yoAAAAJ&hl=tr&oi=ao', 'https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Bilge-Aksay-3', '', '$2y$10$OOG43X83txf.M0EJ5iw1Veu.oclNelUsOwfJ7dqpawXb8W/Viy6pS', NULL),
